      • initCreateObject

        ObjectInit initCreateObject(String containerName,
                            ObjectInit objectInit,
                            String objectGUID)
                     throws ContentAddressableStorageServerException,
                            ContentAddressableStorageAlreadyExistException,
                            ContentAddressableStorageNotFoundException,
                            ContentAddressableStorageDatabaseException
        Initialize object creation Create container on offer if does not exist for one object Also update digest type and object GUID
        Parameters:
        containerName - the container name to create
        objectInit - informations about object to create
        objectGUID - the object GUID to create
        Returns:
        objectInit with the offer object id (needed for the create object operation)
        Throws:
        ContentAddressableStorageServerException - thrown when a server error occurs
        ContentAddressableStorageAlreadyExistException - thrown if the container to create already exists
        ContentAddressableStorageNotFoundException - thrown if the container storage could not be created
        ContentAddressableStorageDatabaseException - thrown if the container sequence could not be incremented

      • createObject

        String createObject(String containerName,
                    String objectId,
                    InputStream objectPart,
                    boolean ending,
                    DataCategory type,
                    Long size,
                    DigestType digestType)
             throws IOException,
                    ContentAddressableStorageException
        Create object on container with objectId Receive object part of object. Actually these parts HAVE TO be send in the great order.
        Parameters:
        containerName - the container name
        objectId - the offer objectId to create
        objectPart - the part of the object to create (chunk style)
        ending - true if objectPart is the last part
        type - the object type to create
        size - inputstream size
        digestType - digest of object
        Returns:
        the digest of the complete file or the digest of the chunk
        Throws:
        IOException - if an IOException is encountered with files
        ContentAddressableStorageException - if the container does not exist
